      "desc": "Fast, nimble, and bristling with guns. The preferred hull for pirates, privateers, and anyone who values speed over staying power. Her shallow draft lets her run into coastal waters where heavier pursuers cannot follow \u2014 and that's saved more pirate crews than any amount of cannon fire.",
      "notes": "The sloop is your glass cannon. She can't slug it out with a frigate, but she shouldn't need to. Use her in chases, boarding actions, and ambushes where her Handling advantage matters. A sloop captain who stands and fights has already lost.",
