      "name": "Bomb Ketch",
      "desc": "A stubby, ugly vessel with two massive mortars mounted forward of the mainmast. She exists to anchor offshore and lob explosive shells over fortress walls. The recoil from those mortars would shake a normal ship apart, so the ketch is built like a bathtub \u2014 thick, heavy, and deeply unpleasant to sail.",
      "notes": "Niche but devastating. The bomb ketch provides indirect fire support that can crack fortifications the players can't assault directly. Use her when the party needs to siege a coastal fort, or when the enemy brings one against the party's harbour. The mortars are terrifying but she's nearly helpless in a ship-to-ship fight.",
