    {
      "name": "Fire Ship",
      "desc": "An old vessel packed with tar, pitch, turpentine, and every other combustible material the dockyard could spare. Light the fuses, aim her at the enemy fleet, and abandon ship. A floating bomb that turns naval tactics on their head \u2014 because even the most powerful ship of the line will break formation to avoid a burning wreck drifting toward her powder magazine.",
      "notes": "The fire ship is a one-use weapon. Build it into a scenario as a desperate gambit \u2014 someone has to volunteer to steer her into the enemy line. The Agility roll to abandon ship before the flames reach the magazine is the dramatic centrepiece. Miss it and you're dead.",
